        <p class="thick">Vem+</p>
        <div class="synopsis">
            The VEM+ network is an interdisciplinary research project based within the Faculty of Social Sciences & Public Policy at King's College London. The project aims to merge visual, embodied and arts-based methodologies with the social sciences. The documentary follows four pairs of VEM+ researchers and artists' collaborative process during a weeklong art residency.  During this time, we get to know their complex treatment of issues of migrant rights, gender justice, the rise in nationalism and post-war reconciliation processes.
            </br></br>
            Find out more about the project <a href="https://www.kcl.ac.uk/research/visual-embodied-methodologies">here</a>.
